lley%20Herford%2C%2063%2C%20thought%20she'd%20be%20retired%20at%20the%20age%20of%2062%2C%20or%20even%2060.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20been%20blessed%2C%20but%20this%20isn't%20what%20I%20expected%20my%20retirement%20years%20and%20pre-retirement%20years%20to%20look%20like%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20drawing%20from%20a%20strong%20pension%20and%20not%20worrying%20about%20anything%20%E2%80%94%20her%20original%20vision%20for%20retirement%20%E2%80%94%20Herford%20is%20still%20punching%20the%20clock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20just%20going%20to%20have%20to%20work%20until%20I%20can't%20work%20any%20longer%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHerford%20spent%20over%2020%20years%20working%20in%20a%20corporate%20role%2C%20an%20aspect%20of%20the%20boomer%20American%20dream%20that's%20become%20out%20of%20reach%20for%20many%20younger%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20after%20suddenly%20getting%20laid%20off%20and%20having%20to%20weather%20the%20pandemic%20years%20with%20intermittent%20jobs%20and%20underemployment%2C%20Herford%20is%20in%20a%20different%20spot.%20She's%20seen%20her%20IRA%20balance%20go%20down%2C%20dipping%20into%20the%20money%20sooner%20than%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20never%20expected%20something%20like%20that%20to%20come%20along%20where%20I%20couldn't%20work%20for%20a%20few%20years%20even%20doing%20nominal%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20I%20was%20living%20off%20of%20my%20savings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHerford%20said%20she%20is%20one%20of%20a%20generation%20who%20did%20what%20they%20were%20supposed%20to%20do%20to%20get%20ahead%20%E2%80%94%20go%20to%20school%2C%20buy%20a%20house%2C%20and%20establish%20a%20career.%20But%20not%20all%20of%20them%20feel%20it's%20paid%20off%20in%20the%20way%20they'd%20hoped.%20Indeed%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-not-enough-retirement-savings-gen-z-millennials-eldercare-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EBI's%20Ann%20C.%20Logue%20reported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20boomers%20aren't%20financially%20equipped%20to%20retire%20right%20now%2C%20with%20a%20solid%20chunk%20holding%20no%20retirement%20savings%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncoa.org%2Farticle%2Fget-the-facts-on-economic-security-for-seniors%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eover%2017%20million%20Americans%20over%20the%20age%20of%2065%20considered%20economically%20insecure%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20did%20everything%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20Herford%20said.%20She%20remembers%20being%20told%20that%2C%20as%20a%20woman%2C%20things%20were%20better%20than%20they%20ever%20used%20to%20be%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20she%20was%20earning%20less.%20She%20said%20she%20was%20told%2C%20%26quot%3BDon't%20ever%20rely%20on%20a%20man%2C%20and%20get%20your%20education%2C%20and%20stay%20with%20the%20same%20company%20and%20work%20hard%20and%20they'll%20reward%20you.%20And%20my%20girlfriends%20and%20I%2C%20we%20all%20took%20that%20to%20heart.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIf%20it's%20bad%20for%20boomers%2C%20it's%20worse%20for%20their%20millennial%20kids%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20days%2C%20Herford%20works%20as%20a%20nanny%20%E2%80%94%20a%20job%20she%20feels%20fortunate%20to%20have.%20She%20was%20able%20to%20buy%20a%20house%20in%20Charleston%2C%20South%20Carolina%2C%20with%20a%20good%20interest%20rate.%20It's%20an%20area%20with%20opportunities%20for%20work%2C%20and%20has%20lower%20taxes%20and%20cost%20of%20living%20than%20the%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20area%20where%20she%20previously%20lived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20she%20thought%20she'd%20have%20more%20of%20a%20cushion%20after%20she%20spent%20years%20saving%20a%20good%20chunk%20of%20her%20pre-tax%20income%20%E2%80%94%20she%20said%20she%20saved%2015%25%20of%20it%20while%20also%20raising%20a%20child%20in%20a%20single-income%20household.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20always%20worked%20on%20the%20weekends%20doing%20whatever%20I%20could%20do%20to%20make%20sure%20I%20maintained%20my%20savings%2C%20thinking%20that%20if%20I%20had%20over%20a%20million%20dollars%2C%20I'd%20be%20set%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20she%20said%2C%20she's%20%26quot%3Bhanging%20in%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20can't%20travel.%20Her%20few%20splurges%20are%20continuing%20to%20have%20some%20streaming%20platforms%2C%20although%20she's%20cut%20out%20a%20few%20of%20those.%20She%20doesn't%20eat%20out.%20She%20tries%20not%20to%20touch%20her%20savings%20unless%20it's%20money%20she%20needs%20to%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20did%20everything%20right%20and%20it%20was%20like%20we%20were%20treading%20backwards%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20going%20backwards.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHerford%20is%20also%2C%20like%20many%20parents%2C%20feeling%20the%20squeeze%20from%20both%20sides%3A%20She's%20trying%20to%20stay%20afloat%2C%20and%20she's%20also%20trying%20to%20ensure%20her%20kid%20does%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20situation%20that's%20becoming%20more%20common%2C%20as%20more%20parents%20support%20their%20young%20adult%20children.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2024%2F01%2F25%2Fparents-young-adult-children-and-the-transition-to-adulthood%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Erecent%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20survey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%203%2C017%20adults%20and%201%2C495%20young%20adults%2C%20conducted%20in%20October%20and%20November%202022%2C%20found%20that%2059%25%20of%20parents%20with%20kids%20ages%2018%20to%2034%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-parents-give-gen-z-millennial-kids-financial-assistance-pew-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efinancially%20assisted%20them%20in%20the%20last%20year%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20turn%2C%20just%2045%25%20of%20young%20adults%20in%20that%20age%20bracket%20said%20that%20they%20were%20completely%20financially%20independent%20from%20their%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20help%20my%20son%20and%20I'll%20help%20him%20as%20long%20as%20I%20can%20because%20these%20millennials%2C%20if%20they%20don't%20get%20together%20and%20have%20roommates%20or%20spouses%2C%20they're%20scraping%20by%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20He%20lived%20with%20her%20briefly%20post-grad%2C%20and%20she%20still%20helps%20him%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20there%20may%20be%20criticism%20over%20older%20parents%20helping%20out%20their%20children%2C%20Herford%20asks%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20are%20we%20supposed%20to%20do%3F%20These%20kids%20came%20into%20a%20time%20when%20corporations%20are%20only%20rewarding%20people%20at%20the%20top.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHerford%20said%20she%20just%20doesn't%20know%20%26quot%3Bhow%20these%20kids%20are%20going%20to%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%20They're%20not%20making%20enough%20money%2C%20they're%20burdened%20with%20student%20loan%20debt%2C%20and%20just%20barely%20scraping%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYes%2C%20boomer%20parents%20are%20helping%20them%20and%20maybe%20it%20will%20upset%20our%20retirement%20plans%2C%20but%20what%20are%20we%20supposed%20to%20do%3F%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20sit%20back%20and%20watch%20him%20not%20be%20able%20to%20go%20buy%20groceries%20because%20the%20cost%20of%20everything%20is%20just%20completely%20out%20of%20control%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20corporations%20are%20being%20very%20greedy.%20I%20think%20everyone%20raised%20their%20prices%20because%20they%20could%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20know%20if%20it's%20going%20to%20stop.%20It's%20just%20a%20travesty.%20It's%20really%2C%20really%2C%20really%20scary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20boomer%20or%20retiree%20struggling%20financially%20or%20supporting%20an%20adult%20child%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajkaplan%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu