t%20and%20Highways%20(MoRTH)%2C%20which%20said%20that%20India%20has%20added%206%2C216%20km%20of%20national%20highways%20in%20April-December%202023.%20This%20is%20only%2045%25%20of%20the%2013%2C800%20km%20construction%20target%20for%20the%20current%20fiscal%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20falling%20short%20is%20not%20new.%20Though%20it%20faced%20a%20target%20of%2012%2C500%20km%2C%20the%20government%20built%20only%2010%2C457%20km%20of%20roads%20in%20the%20fiscal%20year%20of%202022%2C%20and%2010%2C331%20km%20in%202023.%20This%20year%20%E2%80%93%20FY2024%20%E2%80%93%20the%20target%20is%2013%2C800%20km.%20The%20news%20report%20quoted%20an%20anonymous%20source%20in%20the%20know%20who%20said%20that%20achieving%20this%20target%20is%20unlikely%20%E2%80%93%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20India%20has%20added%206%2C216%20km%20of%20national%20highways%20this%20year%20which%20is%20still%20higher%20than%20in%202023%20(when%20only%20about%205%2C744%20km%20of%20work%20was%20completed%20till%20the%20end%20of%20December).%20Sources%20also%20quoted%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20delay%20in%20awarding%20road%20projects%20as%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20why%20highway%20construction%20slowed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20slowing%20down%20has%20come%20despite%20the%20government%20increasing%20its%20capital%20expenditure%20to%20Rs%202%2C15%2C910%20crore%2C%20or%2083.49%25%20of%20the%20record%20high%20capex%20outlay%20of%20Rs%202%2C58%2C606%20crore%20for%20FY2024%2C%20the%20news%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20report%20by%20rating%20agency%20ICRA%20suggests%20that%20highway%20awards%20slow%20down%20in%20the%20last%20quarter%20of%20a%20financial%20year%20that%20comes%20just%20before%20elections.%20If%20this%20happens%20this%20year%20with%20the%20upcoming%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20it%20would%20be%20difficult%20to%20construct%20over%2080%20km%20of%20highways%20every%20day%20in%20the%20last%20three%20months%2C%20the%20news%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707630342000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11105131%2Fyamuna-expressway-385360_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhighway-construction-slows-has-met-only-45-of-its-target-in-current-fiscal-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20has%20added%20only%206%2C216%20km%20of%20national%20highways%20during%20April-December%202023%2C%20against%20a%20target%20of%2013%2C800%20km%20for%20this%20fiscal%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhighway-construction-slows-has-met-only-45-of-its-target-in-current-fiscal-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22FPIs%20on%20bullish%20stance%3B%20infuse%20over%20Rs%2015%2C000%20cr%20in%20debt%20market%20in%20Feb%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707630240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2022-11%2F01%2Ffull%2F1667321312-6946.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Ffpis-on-bullish-stance-infuse-over-rs-15-000-cr-in-debt-market-in-feb-124021100131_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22JP%20Morgan%20Chase%20%26amp%3B%20Co.%20in%20September%20last%20year%20announced%20that%20it%20will%20add%20Indian%20government%20bonds%20to%20its%20benchmark%20emerging%20market%20index%20from%20June%202024%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Ffpis-on-bullish-stance-infuse-over-rs-15-000-cr-in-debt-market-in-feb-124021100131_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Ffpis-on-bullish-stance-infuse-over-rs-15-000-cr-in-debt-market-in-feb-124021100131_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fam