0to%20volunteer%20in%20India.%20Naren%E2%80%99s%20younger%20brother%2C%20Rohit%2C%20is%20an%20aspiring%20film%20producer%20with%20boyish%20charms%20who%20is%20looking%20for%20his%20purpose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%E2%80%99s%20perspective%20isn%E2%80%99t%20limited%20to%20the%20three%20of%20them%20%E2%80%93%20it%20grows%20to%20encompass%20their%20friends%2C%20families%20and%20the%20people%20they%20encounter%2C%20including%20Omkar%20Khaire%2C%20a%20filmmaker%20and%20a%20%3Cem%3Ekaryakarta%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20the%20ruling%20right-wing%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERege%20spoke%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20about%20the%20choices%20she%20made%20in%20her%20book%2C%20how%20its%20central%20theme%20emerged%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYour%20book%20is%20set%20in%20a%20very%20precise%20moment%2C%20right%20after%20the%202014%20elections.%20That%E2%80%99s%20a%20moment%20I%20think%20everyone%20would%20agree%20was%20pivotal%2C%20though%20they%20may%20have%20different%20opinions%20on%20it.%20And%20that%20moment%20still%20feels%20exceedingly%20present%2C%20because%20we%E2%80%99re%20still%20feeling%20the%20impact%20of%20it%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20still%20continuing.%20What%20drew%20you%20to%20this%20as%20the%20setting%20for%20your%20book%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20moment%20might%20be%20precise%2C%20but%20I%20hope%20the%20novel%20feels%20relevant%20to%20a%20much%20longer%20arc.%202014%20brought%20to%20the%20fore%20widescale%20moral%2C%20cultural%20and%20economic%20changes%20in%20Indian%20society%20that%20had%20been%20afoot%20since%20the%20nineties%2C%20if%20not%20before.%20There%20was%20also%20much%20in%20the%20air%20that%20had%20echoes%20with%20other%20democracies%2C%20like%20the%20rise%20of%20conservative%20forces%2C%20the%20fallouts%20of%20late%20stage%20capitalism%2C%20and%20a%20fatigue%20with%20liberal%20ideals.%20As%20a%20writer%2C%20I%20had%20been%20feeling%20into%20these%20anxieties%20with%20my%20early%20work%2C%20and%20the%20election%20clarified%20how%20they%20were%20connected.%20That%20said%2C%20the%20overemphasis%20on%20the%20novel%E2%80%99s%20setting%20often%20makes%20me%20uncomfortable.%20The%20moment%20was%20merely%20a%20frame%20through%20which%20I%20wanted%20to%20explore%20something%20deeper%E2%80%A6like%20the%20psychology%20underlying%20our%20political%20or%20economic%20beliefs%20and%20how%20these%20are%20mediated%20by%20our%20conscience.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20270px)%2085vw%2C%20270px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11100613%2FQuarterlife_FC-768x1215-1.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22270%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11100613%2FQuarterlife_FC-768x1215-1.jpeg%20759w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11100613%2FQuarterlife_FC-768x1215-1-190x300.jpeg%20190w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11100613%2FQuarterlife_FC-768x1215-1-648x1024.jpeg%20648w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696567%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22427%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDevika%20Rege%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EQuarterlife%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EHarperCollins%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20does%20the%20novel%20open%20with%20the%20perspectives%20of%20Rohit%2C%20Amanda%20and%20Naren%3F%20I%20was%20especially%20curious%20about%20Amanda%20as%20an%20American%20in%20a%20story%20set%20in%20India.%20What%20is%20her%20relevance%20to%20the%20novel%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20character%20was%20an%20occasion%20to%20explore%20a%20certain%20worldview%20and%20dimension%20of%20the%20times.%20At%20the%20start%2C%20Rohit%2C%20Amanda%20and%20Naren%20also%20offered%20a%20useful%20triumvirate%20of%20perspectives%20in%20the%20form%20of%20the%20insider%2C%20the%20outsider%2C%20and%20the%20insider-outsider.%20That%20Amanda%20is%20an%20American%20with%20English%20ancestors%20is%20not%20irrelevant%20because%20the%20dynamic%20between%20East%20and%20West%20has%20shaped%20our%20identity%20for%20centuries.%20Since%20liberalisation%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20more%20taken%20up%20with%20the%20US%20than%20the%20UK.%20A%20lot%20of%20middle-class%20kids%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9990s%20grew%20up%20on%20American%20movies%20and%20music.%20The%20brain%20drain%20to%20Silicon%20Valley%20was%20at%20its%20peak.%20Wealthy%20cousins%20who%20went%20to%20the%20States%20for%20a%20summer%20came%20back%20with%20an%20accent.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20like%20to%20admit%20that%20now.%20There%E2%80%99s%20been%20a%20cultural%20shift%2C%20and%20we%20are%20desperate%20to%20destroy%20the%20white%20gaze%20with%20an%20urgency%20that%20both%20Naren%20and%20Rohit%20suffer.%20But%20there%20is%20a%20person%20on%20the%20other%20side.%20What%20happens%20when%20they%20are%20dehumanised%3F%20Does%20it%20liberate%20us%3F%20To%20explore%20such%20questions%2C%20Amanda%20had%20to%20have%20a%20full%20life.%20It%20also%20felt%20important%20that%20she%20isn%E2%80%99t%20simply%20an%20instrument%20for%20the%20Indians%20to%20know%20themselves%20better.%20The%20novel%20may%20be%20set%20largely%20in%20India%2C%20but%20it%20isn%E2%80%99t%20about%20India%20alone.%20If%20it%20was%2C%20it%20would%20be%20a%20simpler%20novel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20a%20scene%20in%20the%20book%20where%20all%20the%20characters%20start%20arguing%20about%20politics.%20Fault%20lines%20that%20were%20already%20starting%20to%20show%20come%20out%20starkly%2C%20and%20the%20argument%20ends%20badly.%20Would%20that%20conversation%20have%20looked%20different%20today%3F%20Would%20it%20have%20happened%20at%20all%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20more%20such%20conversations%20at%20the%20time%2C%20I%20think.%20Whether%20it%20was%202014%20in%20India%20or%202016%20in%20the%20US%20or%20Brexit%2C%20several%20democracies%20were%20witnessing%20a%20period%20of%20acute%20polarisation%20at%20the%20level%20of%20friends%20and%20family.%20Suddenly%2C%20whom%20a%20person%20voted%20for%20seemed%20to%20betray%20something%20essential%20about%20their%20character.%20Whether%20or%20not%20this%20is%20true%2C%20those%20of%20us%20who%20came%20of%20age%20then%20will%20remember%20how%20such%20inflection%20points%20made%20us%20aware%20of%20the%20differences%20among%20our%20closest.%20Now%20the%20filters%20come%20on%20earlier.%20A%20college%20student%20recently%20told%20me%20that%20unlike%20the%20characters%20in%20%3Cem%3EQuarterlife%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20he%20would%20not%20make%20friends%20who%20hold%20such%20different%20views%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20There%20are%20subjects%20that%20families%20have%20banned%20at%20dinner%20and%20on%20groups%20online.%20Dialogue%20has%20entirely%20broken%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EYour%20book%20delves%20into%20the%20interiority%20of%20all%20its%20characters%2C%20often%20telling%20us%20what%20is%20happening%20externally%20through%20their%20perspective.%20What%20drew%20you%20to%20this%20exploration%20of%20interiority%20as%20a%20feature%20of%20the%20narrative%3F%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20choice%20was%20instinctive%20at%20first.%20It%20may%20have%20had%20to%20do%20with%20what%20I%20find%20interesting%20about%20people%20or%20the%20form%2C%20since%20no%20medium%20allows%20you%20to%20inhabit%20the%20minute-to-minute%20thoughts%20of%20multiple%20characters%20in%20language%20quite%20like%20the%20novel.%20But%20as%20I%20kept%20at%20it%2C%20I%20also%20found%20the%20technique%20especially%20relevant%20to%20what%20I%20was%20attempting%20with%20this%20particular%20book.%20It%20pushed%20me%20past%20my%20own%20assumptions%20about%20people%20by%20forcing%20me%20to%20understand%20them%20more%20fully%20than%20if%20I%20had%20written%20them%20only%20from%20the%20outside.%20It%20also%20raised%20uncomfortable%20questions%20about%20representation%2C%20the%20tension%20between%20empathy%20and%20judgment%2C%20and%20between%20ethics%20and%20aesthetics%2C%20many%20of%20which%20felt%20relevant%20not%20just%20to%20art%20but%20to%20our%20responsibilities%20and%20moral%20dilemmas%20as%20everyday%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20voice%20changes%20a%20little%20with%20each%20character%E2%80%99s%20perspective.%20In%20places%2C%20Amanda%E2%80%99s%20voice%20comes%20in%20anecdotes%2C%20almost%20like%20diary%20entries%2C%20while%20Naren%E2%80%99s%20feels%20more%20like%20an%20interior%20monologue.%20There%20is%20also%20a%20change%20of%20literary%20form%20and%20the%20number%20of%20voices%20with%20each%20section.%20Did%20that%20come%20naturally%20as%20well%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20grew%20organically%20in%20that%20each%20movement%20was%20a%20response%20to%20the%20last.%20To%20state%20the%20rationale%20for%20every%20gesture%20would%20flatten%20the%20reading%20experience%2C%20but%20I%20can%20share%20something%20my%20editor%20said%20the%20other%20day.%20She%20described%20%3Cem%3EQuarterlife%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20a%20novel%20that%20endlessly%20mushrooms%20outwards.%20Most%20novels%20introduce%20a%20set%20of%20characters%20in%20the%20first%20half%20and%20resolve%20their%20arcs%20in%20the%20second%2C%20but%20in%20%3Cem%3EQuarterlife%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20new%20characters%20keep%20appearing%20in%20even%20the%20final%20chapters%20and%20reference%20still%20others%20beyond.%20Some%20readers%20have%20found%20this%20exasperating.%20I%20suppose%20it%20defies%20the%20usual%20tenets%20of%20storytelling%2C%20but%20frankly%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20see%20myself%20as%20a%20storyteller.%20Everyone%20is%20peddling%20stories%20these%20days%2C%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20celebrities%2C%20politicians%20or%20brands%2C%20and%20there%20is%20something%20violent%20about%20a%20too-tidy%20narrative%20of%20human%20consciousness%20or%20history.%20As%20I%20understand%20it%2C%20the%20novelist%E2%80%99s