hrough%20his%20later%20plays%20like%20%3Cem%3ECrossing%20to%20Talikota%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20in%20less%20well-known%20writings%2C%20some%20published%20exclusively%20in%20Kannada.%20Among%20these%20are%20two%20short%20stories%20written%20by%20Karnad%20in%20the%201990s.%20One%20of%20them%2C%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EAlida%20Mele%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20takes%20its%20title%20from%20K.%20Shivarama%20Karanth%E2%80%99s%20famed%20novel.%20The%20story%20was%20published%20in%20the%201998%20Deepavali%20special%20issue%20of%20%3Cem%3EKannada%20Prabha%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKarnad%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EAlida%20Mele%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20an%20auto-fictional%20story%20where%20he%20is%20himself%20a%20character%20in%20conversation%20with%20Rizvi%2C%20an%20aspiring%20producer%20who%20wishes%20to%20adapt%20Karanth%E2%80%99s%20novel%20into%20a%20film.%20An%20English%20translation%20by%20Srinath%20Perur%20will%20be%20published%20in%20the%20new%20Bengaluru-based%20literary%20journal%2C%20South%20Parade%2C%20expected%20in%20April%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKarnad%20also%20persisted%20in%20his%20activism%20against%20political%20Hindutva%20and%20the%20mushrooming%20of%20new%20provocations%20after%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20demolition.%20One%20of%20these%2C%20close%20to%20home%2C%20was%20the%20dargah%20of%20Baba%20Budhangiri%20in%20the%20district%20of%20Chikkamagaluru%2C%20a%20place%20revered%20by%20Muslims%20and%20Hindus%20alike.%20In%202003%2C%20the%20dargah%20became%20the%20target%20of%20a%20Bajrang%20Dal%20campaign%20to%20create%20an%20%E2%80%9CAyodhya%20of%20the%20South%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20demanded%20new%20and%20exclusionary%20Brahminical%20rites%20at%20the%20shrine%20and%20called%20for%20the%20removal%20of%20tombs%20nearby%20to%20declare%20it%20as%20an%20exclusively%20Hindu%20religious%20site.%20In%20December%20that%20year%2C%20at%20Karnad%E2%80%99s%20suggestion%2C%20he%20and%20a%20number%20of%20his%20writer%20friends%20went%20to%20Chikkamagaluru%20to%20understand%20what%20was%20happening%20on%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10153153%2Funnamed-5.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22828%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10153153%2Funnamed-5.jpg%20828w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10153153%2Funnamed-5-300x208.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696515%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22573%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ELeft%20to%20right%3A%20Dr%20K%20Marulasiddappa%2C%20Professor%20VS%20Sreedhara%2C%20the%20actor%20and%20writer%20GK%20Govinda%20Rao%2C%20Gauri%20Lankesh%2C%20Shudra%20Srinivas%2C%20and%20Girish%20Karnad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20those%20writers%20was%20the%20newspaper%20editor%20Gauri%20Lankesh.%20She%20was%20an%20unflinching%20critic%20of%20Hindutva%20extremism%20and%20ran%20the%20%3Cem%3EGauri%20Lankesh%20Patrike%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20Kannada%20weekly%20tabloid%20with%20a%20popular%20and%20non-metro%20readership%20across%20Karnataka.%20She%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3ELankesh%20Patrike%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%202003%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSuch%20amazing%20things%20happened%20over%20the%20two%20weeks%20when%20we%20organised%20communal%20harmony%20meetings%20at%20Chikmagalur%20and%20Bababudangiri%2C%20and%20called%20upon%20people%20to%20stop%20Karnataka%20from%20becoming%20another%20Gujarat%20and%20Bababudangiri%20from%20being%20turned%20into%20Ayodhya%20by%20the%20saffron%20brigade%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20their%20visit%20to%20the%20shrine%2C%20Karnad%2C%20Lankesh%20and%20their%20association%2C%20the%20Souharda%20Vedike%2C%20began%20to%20receive%20serious%20threats%20from%20right-wing%20extremist%20groups.%20They%20were%20undeterred%20in%20their%20plan%20to%20make%20a%20second%20trip.%20On%20the%20way%20there%2C%20%E2%80%9CGirish%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20us%20were%20stopped%20midway%20and%20placed%20under%20detention%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20filmmaker%20KM%20Chaitanya%20recalled.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20Gauri%20was%20adventurous.%20She%20didn%E2%80%99t%20come%20with%20us.%20She%20somehow%20smuggled%20herself%20past%20the%20police%20and%20landed%20at%20Baba%20Budangiri.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Modi%20government%20came%20to%20power%20in%202014%2C%20mob%20brutality%20against%20the%20poorest%20of%20Indian%20Muslims%20became%20frequent.%20Regular%20Indians%20came%20together%20to%20protest%20these%20lynchings.%20A%20major%20wave%20of%20civil%20pushback%20was%20the%20%E2%80%98Not%20In%20My%20Name%E2%80%99%20protests%20of%20June%202017.%20The%20event%20in%20Bengaluru%20was%20held%20on%20the%20steps%20of%20the%20Town%20Hall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKarnad%E2%80%99s%20friend%2C%20the%20historian%20Ramachandra%20Guha%20recalled%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGirish%20Karnad%2C%20however%2C%20stayed%20well%20to%20the%20south%20of%20the%20Town%20Hall%E2%80%A6%20He%20was%20in%20his%20late%20seventies%2C%20and%20suffering%20from%20a%20degenerative%20respiratory%20disorder%2C%20which%20obliged%20him%20to%20carry%20a%20cylinder%20at%20all%20times%20which%20sent%20oxygen%20to%20his%20lungs%20through%20tubes%20stuck%20into%20his%20nose.%20I%20did%20not%20expect%20Karnad%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20began%20to%20rain.%20We%20carried%20on%20standing%2C%20in%20the%20open.%20A%20figure%20slipped%20in%20silently%20on%20my%20left.%20It%20was%20Girish.%20He%20had%20walked%20at%20least%20ten%20minutes%20in%20the%20rain%20from%20whichever%20side%20road%20his%20driver%20had%20parked%20his%20car%20in%2C%20carrying%20his%20cylinder%20and%20his%20tubes%20with%20him%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%20Muslim%20men%2C%20in%20the%20row%20in%20front%20of%20us%2C%20murmured%20with%20delight%20and%20approval.%20One%20of%20them%20said%20to%20the%20other%2C%20in%20English%3A%20%E2%80%9CGirish%20Karnad%20Sir%20has%20arrived!%E2%80%9D%20That%20so%20many%20Hindus%20(and%20Christians)%20had%20come%20from%20all%20parts%20of%20the%20city%20mattered%20to%20them%3B%20that%20this%20particular%20Indian%20had%20come%20mattered%20most%20of%20all.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10155158%2Funnamed-6.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10155158%2Funnamed-6.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10155158%2Funnamed-6-300x225.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696519%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EGirish%20Karnad%20at%20the%20protest%20with%20his%20wife%20Dr%20Saraswathy%20Ganapathy%20standing%20behind%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Not%20In%20My%20Name%20protest%20foreshadowed%20what%20would%20be%20one%20of%20Karnad%E2%80%99s%20last%20public%20appearances.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202017%2C%20Gauri%20Lankesh%20was%20assassinated%20by%20suspected%20right-wing%20extremists%20outside%20her%20home%20in%20Bengaluru.%20The%20following%20January%2C%20on%20Gauri%E2%80%99s%20first%20birthday%20after%20her%20assassination%2C%20an%20enormous%20gathering%20of%20citizens%20took%20place%20at%20the%20Town%20Hall.%20The%20memorial%20doubled%20as%20a%20protest%20in%20solidarity%20with%20other%2C%20recently%20jailed%20activists%2C%20who%20were%20being%20smeared%20in%20the%20media%20as%20%E2%80%98Urban%20Naxals%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKarnad%20arrived%20at%20the%20Town%20Hall%20again%2C%20wearing%20a%20cannula%20and%20carrying%20his%20oxygen%20machine.%20Around%20his%20neck%2C%20he%20wore%20a%20sign%20that%20announced%3A%20%E2%80%98Me%20Too%20Urban%20Naxal.%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%9CIf%20speaking%20up%20means%20being%20a%20Naxal%20then%20I%20am%20an%20Urban%20Naxal%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20there.%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20proud%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20the%20hit%20list.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCynicism%20destroys%20our%20infinite%20capacity%20to%20improve%20our%20lot.%20Be%20positive%20and%20you%E2%80%99ll%20find%20your%20inner%20courage.%20I%20hold%20precious%20our%20pluralism%20and%20multiculturalism.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Girish%20Karnad%20in%20a%202004%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20as%20the%20second%20edition%20of%20the%20weekly%20newsletter%2C%20The%20World%20of%20Girish%20Karnad.%20Subscribe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fworldofgirishkarnad.substack.com%2F%3Fr%3Dhzn2u%26utm_campaign%3Dsubscribe-page-share-screen%26utm_medium%3Dweb%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707561362000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10155158%2Funnamed-6.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fhow-advanis-rath-yatra-compelled-girish-karnad-to-enter-politics%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20destruction%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20was%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20Karnad%E2%80%99s%20life.%20%E2%80%9CI%20never%20entered%20politics%20until%20Advani%20started%20his%20Rath%20Yatra%20to%20Ayodhya%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20in%20a%201999%20interview.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A54%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fhow-advanis-rath-yatra-compelled-girish-karnad-to-enter-poli